Aim:
To write a program to demonstrate regular expression operations in Python (match, search, findall, sub) and validate a date pattern.

Algorithm:
S1 - Start
S2 - Import the re module.
S3 - Read the input doc in the format DD/MM/YY.
S4 - Initialize the string p with a general bike-related sentence and set the pattern as "bike".
S5 - Use re.match() to check whether the string p starts with "From" and print the result.
S6 - Use re.search() to check whether the word "bike" is present in the string p and print the result.
S7 - Use re.findall() to find all occurrences of "bike" in the string p and print the result.
S8 - Use re.sub() to replace "bike" with "car" in the string p and display the modified string.
S9 - Extract numbers from the input doc using re.findall("[0-9]+", doc) and print them.
S10 - Validate the format of doc using the regex pattern \d{2}/\d{2}/\d{2}$ with re.match() and print whether it is valid or not.
S11 - Stop
